# clagentic-lite internal-bleed pattern config
# Copy to ~/.config/clagentic/bleed-patterns and add your own patterns.
# One grep BRE pattern per line. Lines starting with # and blank lines are ignored.
#
# The bleed gate scans all committed tracked files for these patterns and blocks
# if any match is found. This catches private strings that must never appear in
# a public repo before they are pushed.
#
# Categories to consider:
#   - Private hostnames (e.g. \.internal\.example\.com)
#   - Internal repo or product names not yet public
#   - Internal tracking IDs if they follow a detectable pattern
#   - Personal email addresses or usernames not for public attribution
#
# Pattern syntax: POSIX BRE (grep -f), one pattern per line.
# Dot (.) matches any character; escape with backslash for a literal dot (e.g. \.host\.example\.com).
# Lines starting with # and blank lines are ignored.
#
# Example entries (all commented out — add your own below):
# \.internal\.example\.com
# my-private-repo
